The music was impeccable. The vocals left something missing. Maybe it was the fact that the power house of an artist Ali Azmat wasnt there or the fact that Ali Noor's vocals werent used to their fullest. Ali Noor is a power house performer too and the fact that he only got to show it towards the end (when he sang the Allah part) was disappointing. He shouldve had more higher notes because the aforementioned Allah part was absolute perfection.
Kind of disappointed. :(

snippet.textDisplay:
Mesmerizing, now this is called complete pacakage. It's on repeat mode from an hour 
or so. Rahat and Ali noor lyrics goes really well together. Salman Ahmad performance and bulk musical arrangements by strings is just love.  Thanks Pakistan for giving us such overwhelmingly tuned people. Those  who are comparing song with Ali's  version are perhaps missing the point of 'evolution and experimentation' in the music industry overall, and  particularly  that coke studio has done over the past 10 years. I think  it was those experiments that made coke studio a globally recognized  music show. More power to you guys....
